      "description": "Calculate similarity score between two strings (0-100).",
      "docstring": "Calculate similarity score between two strings (0-100).\n\nAlgorithm: Levenshtein Distance\n- Measures minimum number of single-character edits needed\n- Edit operations: insertion, deletion, substitution\n- Normalized by string length for percentage score\n\nExamples:\n    calculate_similarity(\"X9K4M2\", \"X9K4M2\") → 100.0 (exact)\n    calculate_similarity(\"X9K4M2\", \"x9k4m2\") → 100.0 (case normalized)\n    calculate_similarity(\"X9K4M2\", \"X9K4N2\") → 83.3 (1 char typo)\n    calculate_similarity(\"X9K4M2\", \"X9K4\")   → 66.7 (2 chars missing)\n\nReturns:\n    Similarity score: 100 = exact match, 0 = completely different\n    \nMatching Thresholds:\n    100%: Exact match → Auto-approve\n    ≥90%: Fuzzy match (1 char typo) → Auto-approve\n    70-89%: Review needed → Flag for manual verification\n    <70%: No match → Reject",
