      "description": "Main reconciliation workflow for CSV uploads.",
      "docstring": "Main reconciliation workflow for CSV uploads.\n\nWorkflow:\n1. Parse CSV with user-defined column mapping\n2. For each row, find best matching token using fuzzy matching\n3. Categorize matches by confidence:\n   - Exact (100%): Auto-create ledger entry\n   - Fuzzy (≥90%): Auto-create ledger entry\n   - Review (70-89%): Flag for manual approval\n   - No match (<70%): Report as error\n4. Update job status and generate report\n\nUse Case:\nThis handles z-Tree and Qualtrics experiments where participants\nmanually entered their tokens into the experimental software.\nManual entry introduces typos which this service auto-corrects.\n\nArgs:\n    csv_content: Raw CSV file content\n    column_mapping: Maps our fields to CSV columns\n        Example: {\"token_column\": \"SessionCode\", \"payoff_column\": \"Points\"}\n    session_id: Session UUID to match tokens against\n    integration_id: Integration configuration\n    org_id: Organization for ledger entries\n    job_id: Reconciliation job ID\n\nReturns:\n    Reconciliation report with statistics:\n    {\n        \"total_rows\": 50,\n        \"exact_matches\": 45,        # Auto-approved\n        \"fuzzy_matches\": 3,         # Auto-approved (high confidence)\n        \"review_needed\": 1,         # Requires manual check\n        \"no_matches\": 1,            # Error - no match found\n        \"ledger_entries_created\": 48\n    }",
